here seems to be an unofficial way that one should pass the same key with multiple values or a key with `[]` after it to indicate that it should be interpreted as a list. Here are the sources that I am getting this idea from [stackoverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3061273/send-an-array-with-an-http-get) and [wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Query_string#Web_forms).\r\n\r\nAs far as I can tell `serde_qs` currently only supports specifying a list by indexing it like:\r\n`/get_method?somelist[0]=a&somelist[1]=b`\r\n\r\nwould it be interesting to also allow both an explicit list indication without an index like this:\r\n`/get_method?somelist[]=a&somelist[]=b`\r\nand an implicit list indication by assigning multiple values to the same field like this:\r\n`/get_method?somelist=a&somelist=b`\r\n\r\nWhat are your thoughts? Some previous discussion can be found here: https://github.com/seanmonstar/warp/issues/733","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/samscott89/serde_qs/issues/35/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/samscott89/serde_qs/issues/35/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Magic-JD/is-fast/issues/40","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Magic-JD/is-fast","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Magic-JD/is-fast/issues/40/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Magic-JD/is-fast/issues/40/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Magic-JD/is-fast/issues/40/events","html_url":"https://github.com/Magic-JD/is-fast/issues/40","id":3001806666,"node_id":"I_kwDON-aqLc6y6-9K","number":40,"title":"Check your connection error when connected to Cloudflare Warp","user":{"login":"mikecsmith","id":10366488,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMzY2NDg4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10